Summary: Provides methods for accessing and modifying the properties of CCDIK joints within a SkeletonModification2D node.

Methods
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_bone2d_node(joint_idx: int) → NodePath
  Gets the Bone2D node associated with the specified joint index.
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_bone_index(joint_idx: int) → int
  Gets the bone index associated with the specified joint index.
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_constraint_angle_invert(joint_idx: int) → bool
  Gets whether the constraint angle is inverted for the specified joint.
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_constraint_angle_max(joint_idx: int) → float
  Gets the maximum constraint angle for the specified joint.
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_constraint_angle_min(joint_idx: int) → float
  Gets the minimum constraint angle for the specified joint.
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_enable_constraint(joint_idx: int) → bool
  Gets whether the constraint is enabled for the specified joint.
* Method: get_ccdik_joint_rotate_from_joint(joint_idx: int) → bool
  Gets whether the joint rotates from the previous joint for the specified joint.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_bone2d_node(joint_idx: int, bone2d_nodepath: NodePath)
  Sets the Bone2D node for the specified joint index.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_bone_index(joint_idx: int, bone_idx: int)
  Sets the bone index for the specified joint index.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_constraint_angle_invert(joint_idx: int, invert: bool)
  Sets whether the constraint angle is inverted for the specified joint.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_constraint_angle_max(joint_idx: int, angle_max: float)
  Sets the maximum constraint angle for the specified joint.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_constraint_angle_min(joint_idx: int, angle_min: float)
  Sets the minimum constraint angle for the specified joint.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_enable_constraint(joint_idx: int, enable_constraint: bool)
  Sets whether the constraint is enabled for the specified joint.
* Method: set_ccdik_joint_rotate_from_joint(joint_idx: int, rotate_from_joint: bool)
  Sets whether the joint rotates from the previous joint for the specified joint.
